---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What Is a Sales Infrastructure Assessment — SalesAtScale.io"
  description="A Sales Infrastructure Assessment identifies every bottleneck in your funnel, calculates your estimated missed revenue, and maps scaling options before you hire."
>
  <!-- Back Nav -->
  <div class="w-full max-w-[1000px] px-6 pt-28 pb-12 mx-auto">
    <a href="/blog/" class="font-chivo text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] hover:text-heading transition-colors flex items-center gap-2 w-fit" style="color:#94A3B8;">
      <span>&larr;</span> Back to Research
    </a>
  </div>

  <!-- Article Hero -->
  <header class="w-full max-w-[1000px] px-6 pb-12 mx-auto" style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(51,65,85,0.6);">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
      <span class="font-chivo font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-xs text-blue">Strategy</span>
      <span style="color:#334155;">|</span>
      <span class="font-chivo font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-xs" style="color:#94A3B8;">March 20, 2026</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="font-chivo font-black text-5xl md:text-[64px] leading-[1.05] tracking-tight mb-12" style="color:#F8FAFC;">
      What Is a Sales Infrastructure Assessment — And Why You Need One Before Hiring
    </h1>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
      <span class="font-chivo font-bold text-lg" style="color:#F8FAFC;">SalesAtScale.io Research</span>
      <span class="font-chivo text-sm" style="color:#94A3B8;">Market Intelligence Team</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Article Body -->
  <main class="w-full max-w-[800px] px-6 py-16 mx-auto">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-[19px] leading-[1.8] font-chivo font-medium" style="color:#94A3B8;">

      <p class="drop-cap" style="color:#F8FAFC;">
        sales infrastructure assessment is a comprehensive analysis of your entire revenue pipeline that identifies every bottleneck in your funnel, calculates your estimated missed revenue, and maps scaling options—before you hire a single rep or SDR.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most 7-figure founders attempt to solve revenue plateaus by throwing bodies at the problem. They hire a new batch of SDRs or bring in an expensive "Head of Sales," only to watch them churn 60 days later because the underlying system was fundamentally broken.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-chivo font-black text-3xl tracking-tight mt-8 mb-2 pb-4" style="color:#F8FAFC; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(51,65,85,0.6);">
        Why you need an assessment before scaling
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="font-bold" style="color:#F8FAFC;">You don't know where the leaks are.</span> Most businesses have thousands of leads sitting in CRM graveyards. Not all of them are dead. An assessment cross-references your current lead flow against follow-up velocities to identify exactly where prospects are falling out of the buying cycle.
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="font-bold" style="color:#F8FAFC;">You don't know your true capacity.</span> The right hiring path depends on whether your current closers are operating at 40% capacity or 95% capacity. An assessment maps the calendar utilization of every rep to determine if you need more leads, or more closers.
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="font-bold" style="color:#F8FAFC;">You don't know your unit economics.</span> Your estimated scaling timeline equals your Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC) vs. your Lifetime Value (LTV). Without a line-by-line analysis of your sales compensation and marketing spend, you're guessing. An assessment calculates the specific numbers from your CRM data.
      </p>

      <!-- Inline CTA -->
      <div class="my-12 py-10" style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(51,65,85,0.6); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(51,65,85,0.6);">
        <p class="text-2xl font-medium leading-snug italic" style="color:#F8FAFC;">
          To understand how these bottlenecks affect your specific revenue goals, <a href="/apply/" class="text-blue font-bold not-italic hover:underline underline-offset-4 transition-all">request an Infrastructure Assessment &rarr;</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        The bottom line is that scaling a broken system only scales the chaos. By auditing the infrastructure first, we ensure that every dollar spent on recruiting, training, and base salaries yields a predictable, trackable return.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- Related Articles -->
  <footer class="w-full bg-surface py-20 mt-12" style="border-top: 1px solid #334155;">
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] px-6 mx-auto">
      <h3 class="font-chivo text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-8" style="color:#94A3B8;">
        Related Articles
      </h3>
      <div class="flex flex-col" style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(51,65,85,0.6);">
        <a href="#" class="flex flex-col md:grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 md:gap-8 py-8 hover:bg-card/30 transition-colors group" style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(51,65,85,0.6);">
          <div class="md:col-span-3 flex flex-col md:pt-1">
            <span class="font-chivo text-[11px] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-blue">Strategy</span>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-8">
            <h4 class="font-chivo text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold leading-tight group-hover:text-blue transition-colors" style="color:#F8FAFC;">
              The Four B2B Sales Hiring Paths — Which Is Right for You?
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-1 flex items-center justify-end text-blue">
            <span class="text-2xl group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">&rarr;</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="#" class="flex flex-col md:grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-4 md:gap-8 py-8 hover:bg-card/30 transition-colors group" style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(51,65,85,0.6);">
          <div class="md:col-span-3 flex flex-col md:pt-1">
            <span class="font-chivo text-[11px] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-blue">Operations</span>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-8">
            <h4 class="font-chivo text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold leading-tight group-hover:text-blue transition-colors" style="color:#F8FAFC;">
              Why Your SDRs Are Churning (And How to Fix It in 30 Days)
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-1 flex items-center justify-end text-blue">
            <span class="text-2xl group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">&rarr;</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .drop-cap::first-letter {
    font-size: 5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: #003BE0;
    float: left;
    line-height: 0.8;
    margin-right: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
</style>
